      "lot_url": "https://www.sixbid.com/en/numiscorner/13392/ancient-greek/11825455/seleukid-kingdom-antiochus-i-soter",
      "title": "Seleukid Kingdom, Antiochus I Soter, Stater, 276-261 BC, Ai-Khanoum, Gold, NGC <br> <br>Seleukid Kingdom, Antiochus I Soter, Stater, 276-261 BC, Ai-Khanoum, Gold, NGC<br>Diademed head of Antiochos I to right, with elderly portrait., Apollo (Delphian/Delphinios Apollo), nude, seated left on the omphalos, testing an arrow in his right hand, his left hand holding the top of a bow resting on the ground to the right; \u2206 in the left field., Graded NGC Ch AU Strike: 4/5 Surface: 2/5; lt.smoothing. Possibly struck in A\u00ef Khanoum or Bactra. Variety 435.3 of Seleucid Coins 435, extremely rare, with only the \u0394 in the field, without the encircling O. Slight traces of plaster in the portrait's hair, remains of an old moulding. A mark on Apollo's face on the reverse, perhaps deliberate. Very rare type, very few examples are held in public collections, and similarly only a few examples have been auctioned for this type in recent years. Beautiful stater, with attractive design, and with a very delicate and precise engraving. The strike, although slightly misaligned, was very sharp, the impression was very well done and all of the engravings are fully visible. From a private English collection (ex Roma Numismatics, Auction XX, 29 October 2020, lot 306)., BA\u03a3\u0399\u039b\u0395\u03a9\u03a3 ANTIOXOY<br>DENOMINATION:Stater                    <br>YEAR:276-261 BC                    <br>COIN CONDITION:Ch AU 4/5-2/5                    <br>MINT NAME:Ai-Khanoum                    <br>COMPOSITION:Gold                    <br>DIAMETER:19.5                    <br>CERTIFICATION:NGC                    <br>CERTIFICATION NUMBER:6639688-005                    <br>OTHER ANCIENT AREA:Seleukid Kingdom                    <br>SC:435.3                    <br>HGC:9-122                    <br>EMPIRE, KINGDOM, OR CIVILIZATION:Ancient Greece, Hellenistic period (323 \u2013 31 BC)                    <br>WEIGHT (G):8.48<br><br>If this product is to be delivered outside of France, it is subject to export authorizations from the Ministry of Culture. This procedure requires a processing time of 2 to 5 months from the date of purchase.<br><br><br>Royaume S\u00e9leucide, Antiochos Ier S\u00f4ter, Stat\u00e8re, 276-261 BC, A\u00ef Khanoum, Or<br>T\u00eate diad\u00e9m\u00e9e d'Antiochos I \u00e0 droite, au portrait \u00e2g\u00e9., Apollon (Apollon Delphien/Delphinien), nu, assis \u00e0 gauche sur l'omphalos, testant une fl\u00e8che dans sa main droite, la main gauche tenant le haut d'un arc pos\u00e9 sur le sol \u00e0 droite ; \u0394 dans le champ gauche., Grad\u00e9 NGC Ch AU Strike: 4/5 Surface: 2/5; lt.smoothing. Possiblement frapp\u00e9 \u00e0 Ai Khanoum ou Bactra. Vari\u00e9t\u00e9 435.3 du Seleucid Coins 435, extr\u00eamement rare, avec seulement le \u0394 dans le champ, sans le O l'entourant. L\u00e9g\u00e8res traces de pl\u00e2tres dans les cheveux du portrait, reste d'un ancien moulage. Un coup sur le visage d'Apollon au revers, peut-\u00eatre volontaire. Type tr\u00e8s rare, tr\u00e8s peu d'exemplaires sont conserv\u00e9s en collections publiques et de m\u00eame, tr\u00e8s peu d'exemplaires ont \u00e9t\u00e9 propos\u00e9s dans les ventes pour ce type ces derni\u00e8res ann\u00e9e. Un tr\u00e8s beau stat\u00e8re, avec une gravure r\u00e9alis\u00e9e dans un style tr\u00e8s fin et d'une grande pr\u00e9cision. La frappe, bien que l\u00e9g\u00e8rement d\u00e9cal\u00e9e, a \u00e9t\u00e9 bien nette, l'impression est tr\u00e8s bien venue et toutes les gravures sont visibles. Provenant d'une Collection Priv\u00e9e Anglaise (ex Roma Numismatics, Auction XX, 29 Octobre 2020, lot 306)., BA\u03a3\u0399\u039b\u0395\u03a9\u03a3 ANTIOXOY<br>VALEUR FACIALE:Stat\u00e8re                    <br>ANN\u00c9E:276-261 BC                    <br>QUALIT\u00c9 DE LA MONNAIE:Ch AU 4/5-2/5                    <br>ATELIER:A\u00ef Khanoum                    <br>M\u00c9TAL:Or                    <br>DIAM\u00c8TRE:19.5                    <br>CERTIFICATION:NGC                    <br>NUM\u00c9RO DE CERTIFICATION:6639688-005                    <br>AUTRE R\u00c9GION ANTIQUE:Royaume S\u00e9leucide                    <br>SC:435.3                    <br>HGC:9-122                    <br>EMPIRE, ROYAUME OU CIVILISATION:Gr\u00e8ce antique, \u00e9poque hell\u00e9nistique (323 - 31 av. J.-C)                    <br>POIDS (GR):8.48<br><br>En cas d'une livraison en dehors de France, ce produit est soumis \u00e0 des autorisations d'exportation par le minist\u00e8re de la culture. Cette proc\u00e9dure n\u00e9cessite un d\u00e9lai de traitement de 2 \u00e0 5 mois \u00e0 compter de la date d'achat.",
